### 5. Retry Logic for External API Calls

**Ambiguous Prompt Patterns:**
- "sends to [service]"
- "calls [API]"
- "posts to [endpoint]"
- No mention of error handling or retries

**Default Retry Strategy:**

```javascript
// ALWAYS implement retry logic for external API calls
async function callExternalAPIWithRetry(templateName, context, body, maxRetries = 2) {
  for (let attempt = 0; attempt <= maxRetries; attempt++) {
    try {
      const response = await $request.invokeTemplate(templateName, {
        context: context,
        body: body
      });
      
      // Success - return immediately
      return { success: true, response: response };
      
    } catch (error) {
      // Determine if error is retryable
      const isRetryable = 
        (error.status >= 500 && error.status < 600) ||  // Server errors
        error.code === 'ETIMEDOUT' ||                   // Timeout
        error.code === 'ECONNREFUSED' ||                // Connection refused
        error.code === 'ENOTFOUND';                     // DNS failure
      
      // If retryable and attempts remaining, retry with backoff
      if (attempt < maxRetries && isRetryable) {
        const backoffMs = 1000 * Math.pow(2, attempt);  // 1s, 2s, 4s
        await sleep(backoffMs);
        console.log(`Retry attempt ${attempt + 1} after ${backoffMs}ms`);
        continue;
      }
      
      // Not retryable or out of attempts - fail
      console.error(`API call failed after ${attempt + 1} attempts:`, error);
      return { success: false, error: error.message };
    }
  }
}

function sleep(ms) {
  return new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, ms));
}
```

**When to Apply:**
- ✅ Webhooks (notification services, automation tools)
- ✅ External API writes (creating records, sending data)
- ✅ Third-party integrations (any service outside Freshworks)
- ❌ Freshworks API calls (platform handles retries)
- ❌ Read-only operations (less critical, can fail fast)

**Decision Rule:**
```
If app makes external API calls:
  → ALWAYS implement retry logic (2-3 retries)
  → Use exponential backoff (1s, 2s, 4s)
  → Retry on: 5xx, timeouts, connection errors
  → Don't retry on: 4xx (client errors), authentication failures
```

