### 7. Event Selection for Serverless Apps

**Ambiguous Prompt Patterns:**
- "on ticket create"
- "when ticket changes"
- "for new tickets"
- Unclear which events to use

**Event Selection Matrix:**

| Prompt Says | Events to Use | Rationale |
|-------------|---------------|-----------|
| "new tickets" | onTicketCreate | Only fires on creation |
| "ticket changes" | onTicketUpdate | Fires on any update |
| "ticket create and update" | Both onTicketCreate + onTicketUpdate | Explicit requirement |
| "escalated tickets" | onTicketUpdate + check priority change | Escalation = priority increase |
| "closed tickets" | onTicketUpdate + check status = closed | Closure is an update |
| "high priority" | onTicketCreate + filter by priority | Create with priority check |
| "status changes" | onTicketUpdate + check status field | Update with status check |

**Event Handler Pattern:**

```javascript
// For "new tickets" or "ticket create"
exports = {
  onTicketCreateHandler: async function(args) {
    const ticket = args.data?.ticket || args.data;
    // Process ticket
    await processTicket(ticket, 'create');
  }
};

// For "ticket changes" or "ticket update"
exports = {
  onTicketUpdateHandler: async function(args) {
    const ticket = args.data?.ticket || args.data;
    const changes = args.data?.changes || {};
    
    // Optional: Check if relevant fields changed
    if (changes.status || changes.priority) {
      await processTicket(ticket, 'update');
    }
  }
};

// For "escalated tickets" (priority increase)
exports = {
  onTicketUpdateHandler: async function(args) {
    const ticket = args.data?.ticket || args.data;
    const changes = args.data?.changes || {};
    
    // Check if priority increased (escalation)
    if (changes.priority && isEscalation(changes.priority)) {
      await processTicket(ticket, 'escalated');
    }
  }
};

function isEscalation(priorityChange) {
  // Priority increased (lower number = higher priority in some products)
  // Or priority name changed to "High" or "Urgent"
  return priorityChange.includes('High') || priorityChange.includes('Urgent');
}
```

**Decision Rule:**
```
If prompt is vague about events:
  → Default to onTicketCreate (most common use case)
  → Add onTicketUpdate if prompt mentions "changes", "updates", or "status"
  → Add priority/status filters in handler if prompt mentions specific conditions
```

