### 8. Field Mapping for External Services

**Ambiguous Prompt Patterns:**
- "map ticket fields to [service]"
- "configurable field mapping"
- "sync ticket data"
- No specific field mapping provided

**Standard Field Mapping Pattern:**

```javascript
// Use this mapping for ANY external service integration
const standardFieldMapping = {
  // Identity (ALWAYS map)
  id: {
    source: 'ticket.id',
    target: 'external_id',
    required: true
  },
  
  // Title/Subject (ALWAYS map)
  title: {
    source: 'ticket.subject',
    target: 'title',
    required: true
  },
  
  // Description/Body (ALWAYS map)
  description: {
    source: 'ticket.description',
    target: 'body',
    required: false,
    transform: (val) => truncate(val, 1000)  // Limit length
  },
  
  // Status (map to external status if possible)
  status: {
    source: 'ticket.status_name',
    target: 'status',
    required: false,
    transform: (val) => mapStatus(val)  // Convert to external status values
  },
  
  // Priority (map to external priority if possible)
  priority: {
    source: 'ticket.priority_name',
    target: 'priority',
    required: false,
    transform: (val) => mapPriority(val)
  },
  
  // Requester (map to external user/contact)
  requester: {
    source: 'requester.email',
    target: 'reporter_email',
    required: false
  },
  
  // Timestamps
  created_at: {
    source: 'ticket.created_at',
    target: 'created_date',
    required: false,
    transform: (val) => new Date(val).toISOString()
  }
};

// Helper: Map Freshworks status to external service status
function mapStatus(freshdeskStatus) {
  const statusMap = {
    'Open': 'open',
    'Pending': 'in_progress',
    'Resolved': 'done',
    'Closed': 'closed'
  };
  return statusMap[freshdeskStatus] || 'open';
}

// Helper: Map Freshworks priority to external service priority
function mapPriority(freshdeskPriority) {
  const priorityMap = {
    'Low': 'low',
    'Medium': 'medium',
    'High': 'high',
    'Urgent': 'critical'
  };
  return priorityMap[freshdeskPriority] || 'medium';
}
```

**Configurable Mapping (iparams):**

```json
// If prompt mentions "configurable mapping"
{
  "field_mapping_id": {
    "display_name": "External ID Field Name",
    "description": "Name of the field in external service for ticket ID",
    "type": "text",
    "default_value": "external_id"
  },
  "field_mapping_title": {
    "display_name": "Title Field Name",
    "description": "Name of the field in external service for ticket subject",
    "type": "text",
    "default_value": "title"
  },
  "field_mapping_description": {
    "display_name": "Description Field Name",
    "description": "Name of the field in external service for ticket description",
    "type": "text",
    "default_value": "body"
  }
}
```

**Decision Rule:**
```
If prompt mentions field mapping:
  1. Use standard field mapping above
  2. Map at minimum: ID, title, description, status, priority, requester, created_at
  3. Add transform functions for status/priority if external service uses different values
  4. If "configurable": Add iparams for field name customization
  5. If "optional mapping": Add iparams with default values
```

