## Quick Reference: Disambiguation Checklist

When encountering ambiguous prompt, check:

- [ ] **Authentication:** OAuth or API token? (Section 1)
- [ ] **Trigger:** Automatic or manual? (Section 2)
- [ ] **Fields:** Are standard fields included? (Section 3)
- [ ] **Payload:** Is structure specified? Use standard if not (Section 4)
- [ ] **Retry:** External API calls need retry logic (Section 5)
- [ ] **UI:** Which Crayons components? (Section 6)
- [ ] **Events:** Which events to use? (Section 7)
- [ ] **Mapping:** Standard field mapping needed? (Section 8)
- [ ] **Validation:** onAppInstall validation added? (Section 9)
- [ ] **Rate Limits:** Throttling needed? (Section 10)

---

## General Principles

### Principle 1: Prefer More Features Over Fewer
When ambiguous, implement MORE rather than less:
- ✅ Automatic + manual trigger (not just one)
- ✅ More standard fields (not just mentioned fields)
- ✅ Retry logic + error handling (not just basic call)

### Principle 2: Follow Platform Best Practices
Even if prompt doesn't mention:
- ✅ Always use Crayons components (never plain HTML)
- ✅ Always implement retry logic for external APIs
- ✅ Always validate in onAppInstall
- ✅ Always include standard fields in logging apps

### Principle 3: Optimize for End-User Experience
When choosing between options:
- ✅ OAuth > API token (for user-facing services)
- ✅ Automatic > manual (for logging/notifications)
- ✅ More fields > fewer fields (for data apps)
- ✅ Better error messages > silent failures

### Principle 4: Make It Production-Ready
Don't build "minimum viable" - build "production ready":
- ✅ Error handling, not just happy path
- ✅ Retry logic, not just single attempt
- ✅ Validation, not just assumptions
- ✅ Rate limiting, not just unlimited calls

